LongDescription: Command Cruisers are Heavy Cruisers by another name.  Heavily armed and armored, they formed the core of most Alliance battlegroups before the Axford-class entered service.  Now, these formerly-mothballed warships provide both the staying power and command and control capabilities that the rest of the Protectorate's fleet lacks.
FlavorText:
CLASSIFIED
PRIORITY
FM PROTECTORATE NAVAL COMMAND//P4R6//
SUBJ/WARSHIP REACTIVATION BRIEF

Bethel has played their hand and it's clear that the Barons are pushing for immediate military buildup in Bethel and Kribensis. It is unlikely that we will secure Kribensis before the Alliance as we lack immediate fleet readiness; however, I have been given the necessary authorization to reactivate the stock of Ocello-class Command Cruisers currently in spacedock around Pyxis and Roclaren. I must make a point that these warships are certified obsolete but a gun is still deadly, no matter the age.

Effective immediately, all mission capable Ocello cruisers will be refit with remaining Alliance stock and Protectorate equipment before being distributed among the Protectorate Navy. Remember: trust in your crew, trust in your vessel.

-O: Constantine
